<subSubSection id="C3616510C407605AFF35CCD698CCFC27" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC407605AFF35CCD6981BFC9E" blockId="4.[189,310,758,784]" box="[189,310,758,784]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<heading id="D08C81F7C407605AFF35CCD6981BFC9E" bold="true" box="[189,310,758,784]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFF35CCD6981BFC9E" bold="true" box="[189,310,758,784]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC407605AFF35CD0598CCFC27" blockId="4.[189,1399,805,937]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C407605AFF35CD0598E6FCB1" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,459,805,831]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFF35CD0598E6FCB1" box="[189,459,805,831]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Polygala tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C407605AFE5DCD069B1FFCCE" box="[469,562,806,832]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C407605AFD5CCD069ABEFCB1" box="[724,915,805,832]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosperma">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFD5CCD069BCBFCB1" box="[724,742,806,831]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFD7FCD059ABEFCB1" box="[759,915,805,831]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">trichosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from it by its internal sepals (wings) with two glands near the rounded apex, and convergent ring of trichomes at the base of the seed (vs internal sepals without glands and with acute apex, and divergent ring of trichomes at the base of the seed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C407605AFE9FCDB098E2FC27" box="[279,463,911,937]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosperma">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFE9FCDB098E2FC27" box="[279,463,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">P. trichosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616510C407605AFF35CDF09DB0FB28" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC407605AFF35CDF09869FC64" blockId="4.[189,324,976,1002]" box="[189,324,976,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
<heading id="D08C81F7C407605AFF35CDF09869FC64" bold="true" box="[189,324,976,1002]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFF35CDF09869FC64" bold="true" box="[189,324,976,1002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC407605AFF35CDDF9DB0FB28" blockId="4.[189,1399,1023,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">
The specific epithet is a reference to 
<collectingRegion id="49BFF879C407605AFDEBCDDF9A38FB97" box="[611,789,1023,1049]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Tocantins State</collectingRegion>
where the species is endemic. Two phytogeographic domains of the state, the Amazon and the Cerrado, are known for large areas of vegetation in a good conservation status. Even though new species from 
<collectingRegion id="49BFF879C407605AFCA4CA659AB3FBD1" box="[812,926,1093,1119]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
are being continuously described (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B6AC407605AFF35CA4898BBFB0C" author="Araujo D. &amp; Antar G. M. &amp; Lombardi J. A." box="[189,406,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="27 - 32" refId="ref5946" refString="Araujo D., Antar G. M. &amp; Lombardi J. A. 2016. Dioscorea compacta (Dioscoreaceae), a new endangered dwarf species from the Jalapao region, Tocantins, Brazil. Kew Bulletin 71: 27 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 016 - 9635 - 8" type="journal article" year="2016">
Araújo 
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFE9ECA499864FB0C" box="[278,329,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B6AC407605AFE2ACA489BAAFB0D" author="Moreira A. L. C. &amp; Antar G. M. &amp; Simao-Bianchini R. &amp; Cavalcanti T. B." box="[418,647,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="146 - 152" refId="ref7020" refString="Moreira A. L. C., Antar G. M., Simao-Bianchini R. &amp; Cavalcanti T. B. 2017. Contribution to the knowledge of Bonamia (Convolvulaceae) in Brazil: a new species and a new occurrence. Phytotaxa 306: 146 - 152. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 306.2.4" type="journal article" year="2017">
Moreira 
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFD80CA499B16FB0C" box="[520,571,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B6AC407605AFD1CCA489ACBFB0D" author="Barbosa-Silva R. G. &amp; Antar G. M." box="[660,998,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="38 - 46" refId="ref6132" refString="Barbosa-Silva R. G. &amp; Antar G. M. 2020. Description vs deforestation: Couepia brevistaminea (Chrysobalanaceae), a new species on the frontier of agricultural expansion in the Brazilian savanna. Phytotaxa 471 (1): 38 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 471.1.4" type="journal article" year="2020">Barbosa-Silva &amp; Antar 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B6AC407605AFC7ACA489D9BFB0D" author="Silva O. L. M. &amp; Antar G. M. &amp; Riina R. &amp; Cordeiro I." box="[1010,1206,1128,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="131 - 136" refId="ref7687" refString="Silva O. L. M., Antar G. M., Riina R. &amp; Cordeiro I. 2020. Euphorbia adenoplicata, a new species of Euphorbia sect. Crossadenia from Brazil. Systematic Botany 45 (1): 131 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364420 X 15801369352388" type="journal article" year="2020">
Silva 
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C407605AFBBDCA499D44FB0C" box="[1077,1129,1128,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="137">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
), the flora of the state is relatively poorly known (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B6AC407605AFDB6CAAC9B91FB28" author="BFG &amp; The Brazil Flora Group" box="[574,700,1163,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="137" pagination="1085 - 1113" refId="ref6305" refString="BFG - The Brazil Flora Group 2015. Growing knowledge: an overview of seed plant knowledge in Brazil. Rodriguesia 66: 1085 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201566411" type="journal article" year="2015">BFG 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and more collecting efforts are in order.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
