<subSubSection id="C3616510C406605BFF35CA359A34FABC" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC406605BFF35CA359BA8FBA1" blockId="5.[189,645,1045,1071]" box="[189,645,1045,1071]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
<heading id="D08C81F7C406605BFF35CA359BA8FBA1" bold="true" box="[189,645,1045,1071]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFF35CA359BA8FBA1" bold="true" box="[189,645,1045,1071]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Distribution, habitat, and phenology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC406605BFF35CA649A34FABC" blockId="5.[189,1399,1092,1330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFF35CA6498E6FBD0" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,459,1092,1118]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFF35CA6498E6FBD0" box="[189,459,1092,1118]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Polygala tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFE5DCA649B1FFBD0" box="[469,562,1092,1118]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
grows in open natural grasslands with scattered shrubs (campo sujo), occasionally near rocky outcrops, on sandy dry soils, sometimes recently burned, at altitudes of 410 to 820 meters alt., in the Tocantins municipalities of Dianópolis and Mateiros (
<figureCitation id="13402A1EC406605BFBA2CAAA9D5DFB2B" box="[1066,1136,1162,1189]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,900,926]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,815]" captionTargetId="figure-12@9.[189,1398,265,818]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Polygala tocantinensis J.F.B.Pastore &amp; Antar sp. nov. A. Inflorescence detail. B. Habit. Photos: G.M. Antar, in situ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5211773" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5211773/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Although considered for now endemic to Tocantins State, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFDE0CA8D9A59FB49" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[616,884,1197,1223]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFDE0CA8D9A59FB49" box="[616,884,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Polygala tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFCF3CA8E9AF8FB46" box="[891,981,1198,1224]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
may also occur in the municipality of 
<collectingCountry id="F36C760BC406605BFF68CAF1986AFB65" box="[224,327,1233,1259]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Formosa</collectingCountry>
do Rio Preto, Bahia State, as the 
<typeStatus id="54C08839C406605BFD66CAF19A0CFB65" box="[750,801,1233,1259]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">type</typeStatus>
collection was made at the division between the two states. Future collecting efforts in a similar physiognomy in Bahia State may prove successful for finding new populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFD88CB389B9AFABF" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[512,695,1304,1329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFD88CB389B9AFABF" box="[512,695,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">P. tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFD37CB389A34FABC" box="[703,793,1304,1330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616510C406605BFF35CB789D60F9FA" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC406605BFF35CB789B66FAFD" blockId="5.[189,587,1368,1395]" box="[189,587,1368,1395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
<heading id="D08C81F7C406605BFF35CB789B66FAFD" bold="true" box="[189,587,1368,1395]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFF35CB789B66FAFD" bold="true" box="[189,587,1368,1395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Preliminary conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC406605BFF35CBA79D60F9FA" blockId="5.[189,1399,1415,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
The estimated Area of Occupancy, with just 
<quantity id="4C839B7EC406605BFD6ACBA79A1EFA2A" box="[738,819,1415,1444]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" unit="km" value="16.0">16 km</quantity>
², is low; the estimated Extent of Occurrence is 
<quantity id="4C839B7EC406605BFF35CB8A9870FA49" box="[189,349,1450,1479]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.831048" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" unit="km" value="1831.048">1831.048 km</quantity>
². This species is known from only four collections in four different localities, with two of these located inside the protected areas of the Parque Estadual do Jalapão and Estação Ecológica Serra Geral do 
<collectingRegion id="49BFF879C406605BFEF9CBD198CAF985" box="[369,487,1521,1547]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
. As is the case with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFD5ECBD19A80F985" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[726,941,1521,1547]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFD5ECBD19A80F985" box="[726,941,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Polygala bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFC3DCBD19D3EF985" box="[949,1043,1521,1547]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, these areas are still subjected to uncontrolled anthropogenic fires and are been rapidly converted to agricultural use. Although still regarded as data deficient, due to the precarious state of conservation of its suitable habitats, the species should be assessed as Endangered EN B1ab(i,ii,iii)+2ab(i,ii,iii) (IUCN 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616510C406605BFF35C8BC9838F8FC" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC406605BFF35C8BC982EF938" blockId="5.[189,259,1692,1718]" box="[189,259,1692,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
<heading id="D08C81F7C406605BFF35C8BC982EF938" bold="true" box="[189,259,1692,1718]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFF35C8BC982EF938" bold="true" box="[189,259,1692,1718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC4369BC406605BFF35C8EA9838F8FC" blockId="5.[189,1399,1738,1906]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFE18C8EA9BB3F96A" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[400,670,1738,1764]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFE18C8EA9BB3F96A" box="[400,670,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Polygala tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFD2EC8EB9A2FF96B" box="[678,770,1739,1765]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFBB3C8EB9DD8F96A" box="[1083,1269,1738,1764]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichosperma">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFBB3C8EB9DD8F96A" box="[1083,1269,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">P. trichosperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with both species sharing the oblong-elliptic capsules with yellow or orange glands along the mid vein and linear leaves. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFE1AC9319B61F8A4" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[402,588,1809,1834]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tocantinensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFE1AC9319B61F8A4" box="[402,588,1809,1834]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">P. tocantinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFDDDC9319B9FF8A5" box="[597,690,1809,1835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFCDBC9319D23F8A5" box="[851,1038,1809,1835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichorperma">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFCDBC9319D23F8A5" box="[851,1038,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">P. trichorperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the characters discussed in the diagnosis. This new species is also superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D18C406605BFC05C9149D4FF8C0" authority="Pastore &amp; Antar, 2021" authorityName="J. F. B. Pastore &amp; Antar" authorityYear="2021" box="[909,1122,1844,1870]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Polygala" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bringelii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90FEA89C406605BFC05C9149D4FF8C0" box="[909,1122,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="138">Polygala bringelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23C57F2C406605BFBE0C9149DEFF8C0" box="[1128,1218,1844,1870]" pageId="5" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see comments above).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
